    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-11-20</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-12-19T20:16:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) increase and make permanent the expensing allowance for depreciable business assets; and (2) allow a tax deduction, up to $10,000, for the purchase of a motor vehicle manufactured in the United States. Terminates such tax deduction after 2010.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to make permanent the deduction for expensing certain depreciable business assets and to allow a deduction for the original purchase of domestically manufactured automobiles.</title>
